Perhaps a bit overkill, but could add an explicit sanity check that the long string is in fact longer than the small string optimization capacity of the small_string type. Something like
template <typename T> struct small_string_inplace_capacity;
template <uint32_t N> struct small_string_inplace_capacity<small_string<N>> {
    constexpr static size_t size = N;
};
EXPECT_GREATER(moved_into_long.size(), small_string_inplace_capacity<string>::size);
and vice versa for the string expected to be smaller than the small string capacity.
(or just use something like string().capacity() if it reflects the small string buffer size)

